cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) techniques for lane detection, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV sub-category. The use of deep learning techniques and Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) also suggests that it may belong to the cs.LG (machine learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel data enhancement method, which could fall under the cs.AI (artificial intelligence) sub-category. The application of the lane detection model in complex scenarios suggests that it may also belong to the cs.RO (robotics) sub-category. Finally, the use of style transfer techniques for enhancing low-light images could also suggest that the paper belongs to the cs.MM (multimedia) sub-category.
